<br>
As such, I see lots of monks, maybe they just don't get around to goodie guilds as much, since most of the monks I do see are Iksar. <br>
<br>
I see tons of clerics. I would not be surprised if a full third of them at any one time are bots however. Every small guild needs two more...and all the large guilds need a dozen more. there are lots...but lots more are needed.<br>
<br>
Warriors and rogues are the answer as to what is lacking. I suspect that every rogue of any talent is known by half the server. They just aren't out there. And as for warriors. <br>
<br>
Wow. Just not enough. Ask the clerics. I keep every warrior of any talent on my friends list, and it's as small now as it ever has been. They just are not out there. You don't HAVE to have a warrior is what people always tell me...yeah well ya know what, go get me a warrior. I want a brick wall planted right there. I want a righteous fury that does not move till the opponent is dead and laughs at it's best shots and keeps on going. I don't want the 4 person chain of slow dying paladins, or shadow knights...or the 12 person speed bump which was the Ranger Patrol as the casters evaced or ran. And I really don't want to hear the 35 non-warrior, high dps, cant take 4 shots from the mob, types bitching about how long the warrior takes to do something, or why aren't they here yet, or how their own grandma the chanter once tanked Venril Sathir from her wheelchair. Get me a warrior, and get the hell outta our way.<br>
