<br>
So, why are more than one warrior need on high end encounters?  Do they typically engage more than one tough target at a time?  Do the healers have no chance of keeping the first one alive so you really need a couple of back ups?  I've been told that my posting tone is &quot;pompous&quot;, so let me say that I am asking sincerely.  I'd really like to know.<br>
<br>
   It is my current understanding that warriors bring 2 things to the table that other classes lack.  They have the best HPs if they are similary equipped, and they have some sort of defensive discipline that keeps them alive against nasty targets.  They are not stars of DPS.  They are built to take punishment, lots of it, but not really dish it out compared to other classes.  I am willing to concede that my current understanding might well be bugged.  But if it is, I would be willing to bet that alot of other people's are too, which might explain a lack of warriors on this server (if that is the way things are).<br>
<br>
    Anyways, even if I concede that several warriors are needed on a high end raid, I am still inclined to say that they are not essential in the rest of the battle situations that come up.  In a duo or experience or LDoN group, a knight class works just as well or better than a warrior.   True, a warrior's higher HPs will in general make a CHeal more mana efficient.  But the others have form of agro management  and crowd control (and here I am specifically thinking of the snare that SK's get that makes rooting to park runners less needed) that might make up for the loss of mana.  <br>
<br>
None of this matters, of course, to the player whos primary aim is to spend as much time possible in high end raids.  But I would hazard to guess that even ardent raiders do others things when there are no raids going on.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
