<br>
Such as the REALLY high level stuff, though there's only a handful of guilds fighting that on FV.  Upper level SSra+.  Where there's anything from 1 unmezzable thing that hits hard to a dozen unmezzable things that hit hard, they need to be offtanked.  Warriors with defensive are nice here, though usually paladins can hold their own as well.  Shadowknights, to my knowledge, don't get the heals and stuns to tank as well as the paladin.<br>
<br>
In the VERY, VERY last stages of PoP, stuff just hits so hard you can't keep a warrior up also.<br>
<br>
The ability warriors get, is /disc defensive.  It is a 3 minute discipline, with a base reuse time of 15 minutes.  This drops a bit I believe, as a warrior levels past the level he gets the discipline.  Warriors don't take as much damage, but it's coded to also make them DO less damage. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dessirra>dessirra</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 330<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/29/03 2:21 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4949.topic&index=40>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: More about warriors...</span><hr size=1> Warriors, followed by any other melee class.  I am soooo tired of group stuck simple because there isn't enough melee to go around.  Go to BB, since LDoN came out everynight it is the same. . .group looking for tanks.  *sighs* <br>
